00:00:21:060000.Speaker: Policeman
00:00:21:060000.Dialogue: Your friend here called 911 to report a robbery.

00:00:23:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:23:120000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, what did they get?

00:00:25:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:25:100000.Dialogue: What didn't they get? They got my enchanted weapons, my vicious gladiator armor, my wand of untainted power, and all my gold!

00:00:35:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:35:230000.Dialogue: You called the police because someone hacked your World of Warcraft account?

00:00:40:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:40:120000.Dialogue: What choice did I have? The mighty Sheldor, level 85 blood elf, hero of the Eastern kingdoms, has been picked clean, like a carcass in the desert sun.

00:00:53:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:53:100000.Dialogue: Plus, the FBI hung up on me.

00:01:13:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:13:200000.Dialogue: Wait a minute! You're not going to do anything?

00:01:22:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:22:230000.Dialogue: Not the kind with access to drugs.

00:01:26:160000.Speaker: Policeman
00:01:26:160000.Dialogue: Fine. Dr. Cooper. I'm sorry for your loss, but the Pasadena Police Department doesn't have jurisdiction in... Pandora.

00:01:39:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:39:190000.Dialogue: World of Warcraft takes place in Azeroth. Goodness gracious, how are you allowed to carry a gun?

00:01:45:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:45:190000.Dialogue: Can you at least refer me to a rogue ex-cop?

00:01:51:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:51:040000.Dialogue: Wh-- you know, one who was drummed off the force because he refused to play by the rules, and now he hires himself out to impose his own brand of rough justice?

00:02:11:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:11:210000.Dialogue: What kind of world do we live in, where a man would take another man's battle ostrich?

00:02:20:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:20:040000.Dialogue: This act of aggression must be met with swift and cruel ferocity. It is time to cry havoc, and let slip the dogs of war.

00:02:28:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:28:180000.Dialogue: I'm on it. Hi, Mrs. Wolowitz. Is, is Howard there? Okay, thanks. That particular dog of war will have to call you back after his bath.

00:02:47:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:47:060000.Dialogue: See if Raj is done with Pilates.

00:03:15:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:15:070000.Dialogue: Three thousand hours. Three thousand hours clicking on that mouse, collecting weapons and gold. It's almost as if it was a huge waste of time.

00:03:27:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:27:060000.Dialogue: Whoever did this knew what they were doing. He got in and out of your account in under 15 minutes, transferred all your stuff, and didn't leave a digital fingerprint.

00:03:34:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:34:160000.Dialogue: Oh! There isn't enough chamomile tea in the world to quell the rage in my heart.

00:03:42:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:42:120000.Dialogue: Hold on. I'm talking to an orc under the bridge in Thunder Bluff who says if we pay him, he'll help us track down your things.

00:03:49:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:49:230000.Dialogue: I should say so; he appears to be a member of the Nigerian royal family.

00:03:56:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:56:150000.Dialogue: Whoa! Somebody's auctioning off a jeweled ostrich bridle!

00:04:02:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:02:040000.Dialogue: He was a simple ostrich. Is! Is, I haven't given up hope.

00:04:10:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:10:030000.Dialogue: Hey, Penny. We're kind of in the middle of a crisis, here.

00:04:12:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:12:090000.Dialogue: Oh, I know. Bernadette told me. Sorry, Sheldon. I know that game meant a lot to you. What--

00:04:21:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:21:060000.Dialogue: Excuse me, Penny, but Doodle Jump is a game. Angry Birds is a game. World of Warcraft is a massively multi-player online role-playing... all right, technically it's a game.

00:04:36:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:36:160000.Dialogue: Bad news, the Nigerian prince may be a fraud.

00:04:40:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:40:090000.Dialogue: Okay, well, anyways, I brought you a day-old cheesecake to cheer you up!

00:04:44:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:44:030000.Dialogue: Stale pastry is hollow succor to a man who is bereft of ostrich.

00:04:59:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:59:000000.Dialogue: Oh, hi! I was just dropping off a cheesecake to Sheldon. He was robbed of a bunch of imaginary crap that's useful in a make-believe place.

00:05:07:210000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:07:210000.Dialogue: I don't know what that means.

00:05:14:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:14:100000.Dialogue: Did you know last weekend Priya took Leonard rollerblading at the beach? Can you believe that?

00:05:19:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:05:19:140000.Dialogue: I feel like I'm supposed to say "that bitch," but I don't have enough information.

00:05:25:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:25:020000.Dialogue: I am the one who spent two years trying to get him to even go to the beach in the first place. And he was so phobic about stepping on medical waste, I had to carry him to the water.

00:05:34:060000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:05:34:060000.Dialogue: I took Howard to the beach once. He almost burst into flames like a vampire.

00:05:41:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:41:020000.Dialogue: So what's the thanks I get for turning Leonard into quality boyfriend material? I have to tiptoe around his new girlfriend.

00:05:53:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:53:230000.Dialogue: Want some coffee liqueur on your ice cream?

00:05:56:180000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:56:180000.Dialogue: Ah, here's the alcohol and drug peer pressure Mother warned me about.

00:06:02:060000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:02:060000.Dialogue: I was starting to think it was never going to happen. Yes, please.

00:06:07:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:07:170000.Dialogue: You guys should've seen Leonard when I first met him. There was no eye contact. He was either looking up at the ceiling, or down at his shoes.

00:06:17:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:17:050000.Dialogue: You know, for the first couple of months, whenever I would take off my bra, he would giggle and say, "Oh, boy, my breast friends!"

00:06:25:210000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:25:210000.Dialogue: Well, if it makes you feel any better, I'm never speaking to Priya again.

00:06:30:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:30:020000.Dialogue: No, don't do that. No reason to be mean to her.

00:06:32:160000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:32:160000.Dialogue: This may be the alcohol talking... but I believe there is. Are you familiar with the recent study of Tanzanian chimpanzees by Nishida and Hosaka out of Kyoto University?

00:06:44:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:44:040000.Dialogue: No, but I can name all the Kardashians.

00:06:47:100000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:47:100000.Dialogue: Primates, such as ourselves, have a natural instinct to ostracize ill-mannered members of the troop. Bernadette's urge to shun, scowl or fling her waste at Priya is hard-wired into her DNA.

00:06:59:080000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:59:080000.Dialogue: I don't have an urge to fling my waste.

00:07:03:060000.Speaker: Amy
00:07:03:060000.Dialogue: Believe me, it's there, we all have it. Hit me with some more booze, and I'll show you.

00:07:10:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:10:220000.Dialogue: All right, here we are-- this is the tavern where all the black-market weapon trades go down.

00:07:16:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:16:200000.Dialogue: I don't think my character should be in a place like this. Everyone's undressing her with their eyes.

00:07:21:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:21:200000.Dialogue: Maybe if you stop dropping your sword and bending over to pick it up.

00:07:27:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:27:160000.Dialogue: Okay, what exactly are we looking for?

00:07:29:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:29:070000.Dialogue: Redheaded troll, goes by the name of Glumly. According to the message boards, if you want to move stolen goods and it's after school hours, he's your guy.

00:07:36:020000.Speaker: Priya
00:07:36:020000.Dialogue: Leonard, is this going to take much longer? I thought we were going to spend some time together.

00:07:40:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:40:140000.Dialogue: Uh, we are. In the meantime, you're welcome to whip up a quick character and join us.

00:07:46:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:46:090000.Dialogue: Well, you have to put in a credit card number, but it's fun.

00:07:50:230000.Speaker: Priya
00:07:50:230000.Dialogue: Maybe I should just go home.

00:07:52:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:52:170000.Dialogue: Our troll just walked in! I got him!

00:07:54:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:54:050000.Dialogue: We got him. We're almost done.

00:07:56:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:56:010000.Dialogue: So, how do you guys want to play this?

00:07:58:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:58:080000.Dialogue: Be ruthless. You tell him if he doesn't start talking, we'll register a complaint with his Internet service provider.

00:08:05:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:05:020000.Dialogue: Sheldon, what if he gets his Internet from his cable company? He could lose his HBO and all their delightful original programming.

00:08:13:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:13:120000.Dialogue: I don't care! I'm losin' it, man!

00:08:16:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:16:200000.Dialogue: Why don't we play this smart? Try a little "good goblin, bad goblin."

00:08:22:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:22:160000.Dialogue: Nah, I think we have to be more subtle.

00:08:24:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:24:230000.Dialogue: Okay, I see where this is going. Fine, I'll have sex with him.

00:08:32:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:32:090000.Dialogue: That's not where it was going.

00:08:35:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:35:140000.Dialogue: Good, because I would hate that.

00:08:40:190000.Speaker: Priya
00:08:40:190000.Dialogue: Leonard, you're busy-- let's talk tomorrow.

00:08:42:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:42:090000.Dialogue: Oh, wait. - Hang on. Are you upset?

00:08:43:190000.Speaker: Priya
00:08:43:190000.Dialogue: - No, no, I think it's sexy to date a boy trapped in a man's body.

00:08:54:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:54:190000.Dialogue: And people think I don't get sarcasm.

00:09:08:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:08:120000.Dialogue: Hi. We're just heading out for a drink.

00:09:14:090000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:14:090000.Dialogue: Count your blessings you're not a Tanzanian chimp.

00:09:19:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:19:190000.Dialogue: Don't listen to her-- she's had a lot of ice cream.

00:09:23:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:23:090000.Dialogue: Do you want to join us?

00:09:24:150000.Speaker: Priya
00:09:24:150000.Dialogue: Oh, thank you, but I have work to do.

00:09:29:090000.Speaker: Amy
00:09:29:090000.Dialogue: Four women walk down the stairs-- how many reach the lobby?

00:09:40:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:40:160000.Dialogue: Did your sister say anything when you got home last night?

00:09:43:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:43:070000.Dialogue: Oh, no, don't put me in the middle of this. I'm not going to be your go-between.

00:09:47:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:47:070000.Dialogue: Come on, help me out. Am I in trouble?

00:09:52:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:52:230000.Dialogue: I'm sure many women in happy relationships spend their nights Skyping with their ex-boyfriend Sanjay.

00:10:01:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:01:210000.Dialogue: Good news, gentlemen-- I found our hacker.

00:10:05:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:05:100000.Dialogue: Yeah. No one can hide from me, not Waldo, not Carmen San Diego, not even topless Natalie Portman.

00:10:12:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:12:060000.Dialogue: I've never said these words before, but good job, Howard!

00:10:17:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:17:120000.Dialogue: Thanks. Our culprit is one Mr. Todd Zarnecki, 2711 Ocean View Road, Carlsbad, California.

00:10:24:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:24:170000.Dialogue: The name and the address drip with evil.

00:10:27:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:27:170000.Dialogue: What else do we know about him?

00:10:30:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:30:210000.Dialogue: I'll bet he's some loser who lives with his parents.

00:10:38:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:38:140000.Dialogue: Yes, he does live with his parents. Here's a Google Earth shot of their house.

00:10:45:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:45:140000.Dialogue: Excellent! It's in a cul-de-sac. We can box him in.

00:10:48:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:48:170000.Dialogue: Hold on, you're thinking of going there?

00:10:51:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:51:150000.Dialogue: Carlsbad is only a couple of hours away.

00:10:53:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:53:230000.Dialogue: Fine. You walk up to the house, knock on the door and demand your stuff back. What if he says no?

00:10:59:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:59:000000.Dialogue: I don't know if you've been following the news, Leonard, but there have been some terrific advancements in the field of torture.

00:11:08:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:08:030000.Dialogue: Fine, we'll abide by the Geneva Convention. But ask yourself this: in the course of our lives, how much lunch money has been taken from us? How many kites? How many Scooby-Doo Trapper Keepers?

00:11:21:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:21:080000.Dialogue: I totally had one of those.

00:11:22:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:22:190000.Dialogue: Of course you did. It was a fun and practical way of organizing your school work. But the bullies took it from us. Well, no more.

00:11:30:020000.Speaker: sheldon
00:11:30:020000.Dialogue: Tonight, we take back our dignity, our birthright and our pride. What do you say? Who's with me?

00:11:41:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:41:030000.Dialogue: I have a hip-hop aerobics class at 5:00; could we go after?

00:11:47:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:47:170000.Dialogue: Also, tonight's the Sabbath and my mother and I have a tradition of lighting the candles and watching Wheel of Fortune, so... If we could leave at 8:00, we'd still be able to regain our birthright at 10:00, 10:30 latest.

00:12:00:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:00:200000.Dialogue: Oh, geez, I-I don't know if I can ditch Priya two nights in a row.

00:12:04:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:04:200000.Dialogue: Oh, come on, man. Bros before...

00:12:25:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:25:060000.Dialogue: I'm hell-bent on catching a cyber criminal, not the common cold.

00:12:32:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:32:230000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, I thought this delay was so you could watch Wheel of Fortune with your mother.

00:12:37:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:37:090000.Dialogue: I am. She's just bleaching her mustache.

00:12:41:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:41:030000.Dialogue: Check it out. Hey, Ma! "Before and After!" Four words, 17 letters, two N's, one V!

00:12:53:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:53:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, she's kind of a Wheel savant.

00:13:00:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:00:170000.Dialogue: Sitar music for her ringtone is not cool, dude.

00:13:04:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:04:060000.Dialogue: Hit the... Hey, sweetie. Yeah, I'm sorry. I'm gonna be working late.

00:13:14:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:14:050000.Dialogue: Yeah, I-I miss you, too. Okay, sure, I'll call you when I get home. Okay, bye-bye.

00:13:20:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:20:180000.Dialogue: Very nice. You lie to my sister.

00:13:25:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:25:040000.Dialogue: That's the nicest thing he does to your sister.

00:13:39:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:39:180000.Dialogue: Hello, Priya. What's up? How would I know if Leonard's at work or not? Don't be suspicious. Look, if you want your relationship with Leonard to continue, you're going to have to believe whatever wild-eyed, cockamamie excuse the white devil has the nerve to offer you.

00:14:01:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:01:210000.Dialogue: New puzzle, Ma! Same name! One N, two D's, three O's!

00:14:10:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:10:200000.Dialogue: I know. It's her superpower. Well, that and jiggling her arm fat.

00:14:17:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:17:120000.Dialogue: I can't believe we're going all the way to San Diego to confront this guy.

00:14:21:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:21:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, we're kind of bad-asses, aren't we?

00:14:25:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:25:220000.Dialogue: Hey, how about we stay the night and hit Legoland in the morning?

00:14:30:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:30:060000.Dialogue: Sea World is better. It has Shamu, who is literally tons of fun. But for the moment, let's stay focused on Todd Zarnecki.

00:14:39:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:39:040000.Dialogue: Yeah, we're coming for you, Todd Zarnecki. And for the record, Legoland is more interactive.

00:14:46:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:46:000000.Dialogue: I almost feel sorry for the poor fool, sitting in his split-level suburban ranch, unaware that a vengeful horde is barreling down the San Diego Freeway at 71 miles an hour. Ease up there, lead foot. You trying to get us killed?

00:15:02:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:02:200000.Dialogue: I took the liberty of burning us a mix of heroic questing music.

00:15:12:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:12:200000.Dialogue: It's a re-writable CD. Just put it in.

00:15:18:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:18:040000.Dialogue: She's curvy and she owns it. I like that.

00:15:31:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:31:230000.Dialogue: We are winged fury! Which is still no excuse for going over the posted speed limit.

00:15:43:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:43:090000.Dialogue: Next time we go to kick someone's ass, we take the train.

00:16:01:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:01:160000.Dialogue: No weapon strikes more fear into a man's heart than a Klingon bat'leth.

00:16:06:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:06:170000.Dialogue: Okay, let's get clear on something. We're just going to tell this guy to transfer all of your stuff back into your account and then be on our way. No one's bat'lething anybody.

00:16:18:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:18:060000.Dialogue: So my blade shall not taste blood tonight?

00:16:23:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:23:170000.Dialogue: Well, now I just feel silly holding it.

00:16:28:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:28:230000.Dialogue: Can I at least kick down the door?

00:16:31:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:31:190000.Dialogue: You're welcome to try, but the other day, it took you 15 minutes to get into a FedEx box.

00:16:43:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:43:130000.Dialogue: Don't say "your doom." Who opens the door for their doom?

00:17:04:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:04:170000.Dialogue: I am Sheldor of Azeroth. I want my things back.

00:17:08:130000.Speaker: Todd
00:17:08:130000.Dialogue: I don't think so. Let me see that.

00:17:12:040000.Speaker: Todd
00:17:12:040000.Dialogue: I know. I've always wanted one.

00:17:23:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:23:230000.Dialogue: Well, he's even more cunning than we thought.

00:17:31:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:31:090000.Dialogue: You know, the joke's on him. Without the certificate of authenticity, that bat'leth is worthless.

00:17:38:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:38:070000.Dialogue: Yeah, he walked right into our trap.

00:17:42:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:42:200000.Dialogue: Legoland seems like a hollow dream now.

00:18:10:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:10:050000.Dialogue: Well, we'd better call somebody to come pick us up. It'd be swell if they had a train.

00:18:23:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:23:100000.Dialogue: No problem. So, Leonard, I think it's interesting you didn't call your girlfriend to come get you.

00:18:30:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:30:140000.Dialogue: Uh, I kind of told her I was working.

00:18:33:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:33:020000.Dialogue: So you lied to her. Also interesting.

00:18:36:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:36:180000.Dialogue: Yeah, she doesn't really understand the whole Warcraft adventure-role-playing thing.

00:18:41:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:41:110000.Dialogue: Well, doesn't matter if she gets it, as long as she's pretty.

00:18:46:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:46:070000.Dialogue: This one's funny, Leonard. How come you couldn't make it work with her?

00:18:52:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:52:100000.Dialogue: So did you at least get Sheldon's fake stuff back?

00:18:55:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:55:000000.Dialogue: No. We failed in our noble quest.

00:19:05:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:05:220000.Dialogue: I'm gonna show you how we finish a quest in Nebraska.

00:19:26:090000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:26:090000.Speaker: Todd

00:19:29:130000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:29:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:29:130000.Dialogue: Give my friend his stuff back.

00:19:31:060000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:31:060000.Speaker: Todd
00:19:31:060000.Dialogue: I don't know what you're talking about.

00:19:33:030000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:33:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:33:030000.Dialogue: Well, then, good news. Today's the day a girl's finally going to touch you in your little special place.

00:19:41:070000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:41:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:41:070000.Dialogue: Now give him his stuff back.

00:19:43:190000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:43:190000.Speaker: Todd

00:19:45:080000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:45:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:19:48:130000.Scene: Todd Zarnecki’s house. Todd answers the door.
00:19:48:130000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:20:50:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:50:080000.Dialogue: All right, well, great seeing you.

00:20:55:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:55:220000.Dialogue: Amy's right. I do want to fling my poop at her.
